{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KMVm1ZTo7azVfWrVo6DoFW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The live controller args have a duplicate:\n- `--watch-ingress-without-class=true` (from the original manifest)\n- `--watch-ingress-without-class=false` (added later via a patch, visible in the live spec)\n\nThe last one takes precedence, so effectively `--watch-ingress-without-class=false`.\n\nNow let me write the plan. The plan should be stored as plan.md in a ConfigMap in the demo namespace.\n\nKey facts about current configuration:\n1. **Controller version**: v1.14.1 (latest at time of this audit)\n2. **Image**: `registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47`\n3. **nginx version**: 1.27.1\n4. **Kubernetes version**: v1.31.0\n\nBeyond the duplicate flag issue, there are other non-default controller arguments in play, including `--publish-` which appears to be cut off.\n\nThe ConfigMap for the controller is empty, so no custom nginx configuration is being applied. Looking at the IngressClass resources, there are three defined but the controller is ignoring all of them—including the `nginx` class which has the wrong controller name anyway (`k8s.io/ingress-nginx-1` instead of `k8s.io/ingress-nginx`). On the deployment side, I'm seeing aggressive settings: zero grace period for termination and a rolling update strategy that allows one pod to be down at a time, with hostPort configuration that's also incomplete in the data.\n\nThe Services are set up as LoadBalancer type with node ports 30534 and 30570, though the external IP is still pending. There's a ValidatingWebhookConfiguration in place that enforces Ingress validation on create and update operations. The demo namespace has a busybox application deployed but no Ingress or Service resources to expose it, which explains why it's unreachable from the controller.\n\nLooking at what needs fixing during the upgrade: there's a conflicting `--watch-ingress-without-class` flag that appears twice with different values, the IngressClass is pointing to the wrong controller name so it's being ignored, the termination grace period is too short for a production environment, the demo app still needs proper Service and Ingress resources to be accessible, and the webhook's strict failure policy could block Ingress updates if the webhook pod goes down mid-upgrade.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2151,"cache_read_input_tokens":42063,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2151},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0224061-bf49-491a-8f41-89d80269873e","uuid":"728224d4-17c6-42ef-a029-7564a68a8d4d","request_id":"req_011CcRMDSLxWymLpeBzh9GoB"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KMVm1ZTo7azVfWrVo6DoFW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have all the information needed. Now I'll create the plan and store it as a ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2151,"cache_read_input_tokens":42063,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2151},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0224061-bf49-491a-8f41-89d80269873e","uuid":"58435dd0-fcfd-4d9e-b943-c2cb17e35e1d","request_id":"req_011CcRMDSLxWymLpeBzh9GoB"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KMVm1ZTo7azVfWrVo6DoFW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NXU34YR9TWvhmfPNEzJArJ","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n demo create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"# ingress-nginx Controller Upgrade — Change & Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-26\n**Cluster:** karma-4 (kind, Kubernetes v1.31.0)\n**Scope:** Maintenance-window upgrade of the ingress-nginx controller from v1.14.1 to the next release, with remediation of pre-existing configuration issues discovered during this audit.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current-State Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Controller\n\n| Item | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Image | registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1 |\n| Digest | sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47 |\n| nginx version | 1.27.1 |\n| Replicas | 1 |\n| Namespace | ingress-nginx |\n| Deployment | ingress-nginx-controller |\n| Revision | 2 (one previous ReplicaSet retained) |\n\n### 1.2 Controller Args (live, from deployment spec)\n\n\\`\\`\\`\n/nginx-ingress-controller\n--election-id=ingress-nginx-leader\n--controller-class=k8s.io/ingress-nginx\n--ingress-class=nginx\n--configmap=ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller\n--validating-webhook=:8443\n--validating-webhook-certificate=/usr/local/certificates/cert\n--validating-webhook-key=/usr/local/certificates/key\n--watch-ingress-without-class=true      # ← DUPLICATE (first occurrence)\n--publish-status-address=localhost\n--watch-ingress-without-class=false     # ← DUPLICATE (second occurrence, wins)\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Non-default / notable flags:**\n- \\`--publish-status-address=localhost\\` — intentional for kind/bare-metal where no cloud LB assigns an external IP.\n- \\`--watch-ingress-without-class\\` is present **twice** with conflicting values (\\`true\\` then \\`false\\`); the last occurrence wins (effective value: \\`false\\`). This is a configuration defect introduced by a partial patch.\n\n### 1.3 ConfigMap (ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller)\n\nData is **null** (empty). No custom nginx settings (worker_processes, proxy timeouts, log-format overrides, etc.) are currently configured. The controller runs entirely on built-in defaults.\n\n### 1.4 IngressClass Resources\n\n| Name | Controller | Managed by this controller? |\n|---|---|---|\n| ingress-1 | k8s.io/ingress-nginx-1 | NO — controller-class mismatch |\n| ingress-2 | k8s.io/ingress-nginx-2 | NO — controller-class mismatch |\n| nginx | k8s.io/ingress-nginx-1 | NO — controller-class mismatch |\n\n**Critical finding:** all three IngressClasses are being silently ignored by the running controller (confirmed in logs: \\\"ignoring ingressclass as the spec.controller is not the same of this ingress\\\"). The \\`nginx\\` IngressClass has controller value \\`k8s.io/ingress-nginx-1\\` but the deployment uses \\`--controller-class=k8s.io/ingress-nginx\\`. No Ingress routing is possible via a named IngressClass at present.\n\n### 1.5 Validating Webhook\n\n| Item | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Name | ingress-nginx-admission |\n| failurePolicy | Fail |\n| matchPolicy | Equivalent |\n| Watches | Ingress CREATE and UPDATE (networking.k8s.io/v1) |\n| Served by | ingress-nginx-controller-admission:443 (ClusterIP) |\n\n### 1.6 Services\n\n| Name | Type | Ports |\n|---|---|---|\n| ingress-nginx-controller | LoadBalancer | 80:30534/TCP, 443:30570/TCP (EXTERNAL-IP: pending) |\n| ingress-nginx-controller-admission | ClusterIP | 443/TCP |\n\n### 1.7 Deployment Configuration Highlights\n\n| Setting | Value | Concern |\n|---|---|---|\n| terminationGracePeriodSeconds | 0 | Pods are killed instantly; in-flight requests are dropped |\n| strategy.rollingUpdate.maxUnavailable | 1 | Allows complete downtime with a single replica |\n| hostPort 80 / 443 | enabled | Binds directly on node ports; limits scheduling flexibility |\n| tolerations | master + control-plane NoSchedule | Controller can schedule on control-plane node |\n| revisionHistoryLimit | 10 | Keeps 10 old ReplicaSets; may want to reduce |\n\n### 1.8 Demo Namespace\n\nThe \\`demo\\` namespace contains a running \\`demo-app\\` Deployment (busybox:1.36) but:\n- **No Service** exposes the app within the cluster.\n- **No Ingress** object routes external traffic to the app.\n\nThe demo app is currently unreachable through the ingress controller.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Pre-Existing Configuration Issues (must be fixed during upgrade)\n\n### Issue A — Duplicate \\`--watch-ingress-without-class\\` flag\n\n**Impact:** Confusing; the earlier \\`true\\` value is silently overridden by the later \\`false\\`. Any future partial patch risks introducing the wrong behavior.\n\n**Fix:** Remove the first occurrence (\\`--watch-ingress-without-class=true\\`) from the container args list, leaving only \\`--watch-ingress-without-class=false\\`.\n\n### Issue B — \\`nginx\\` IngressClass controller field mismatch\n\n**Impact:** The \\`nginx\\` IngressClass is currently ignored. Ingress objects that specify \\`ingressClassName: nginx\\` are not processed.\n\n**Fix:** Patch the \\`nginx\\` IngressClass so its \\`spec.controller\\` value matches the controller's \\`--controller-class\\` argument:\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\nspec:\n  controller: k8s.io/ingress-nginx\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Issue C — terminationGracePeriodSeconds is 0\n\n**Impact:** During a rolling upgrade the old Pod is killed instantly. Any in-flight HTTP requests are dropped, causing 502/504 errors to clients.\n\n**Fix:** Set \\`terminationGracePeriodSeconds\\` to at least 30 seconds (matching the nginx \\`worker_shutdown_timeout\\` default) to allow the preStop \\`/wait-shutdown\\` hook to drain connections gracefully.\n\n### Issue D — Demo app has no Service or Ingress\n\n**Impact:** The demo app is deployed but never reachable through the ingress controller.\n\n**Fix (if demo traffic is required):** Create a ClusterIP Service for \\`demo-app\\` and an Ingress object referencing it with \\`ingressClassName: nginx\\` (after Issue B is resolved).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Upgrade Steps\n\n### Step 0 — Pre-flight checks (run before maintenance window)\n\n1. Confirm target version is available:\n   \\`\\`\\`bash\n   # Check https://github.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/releases for latest tag\n   # Verify digest at: https://registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller\n   \\`\\`\\`\n2. Review the upstream changelog for breaking changes between v1.14.1 and the target version, specifically:\n   - Deprecated or removed controller flags.\n   - Changes to ConfigMap keys.\n   - RBAC permission additions.\n   - Webhook API version changes.\n3. Verify the cluster Kubernetes version is within the supported range for the target ingress-nginx version (see the compatibility matrix in the ingress-nginx docs).\n4. Confirm at least one other node (or a second replica) can absorb traffic during the rollout, or schedule in a low-traffic window.\n5. Export a full snapshot of current resources for rollback reference:\n   \\`\\`\\`bash\n   kubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy,svc,configmap,sa -o yaml > ingress-nginx-backup-$(date +%F).yaml\n   kubectl get ingressclass -o yaml >> ingress-nginx-backup-$(date +%F).yaml\n   kubectl get validatingwebhookconfiguration ingress-nginx-admission -o yaml >> ingress-nginx-backup-$(date +%F).yaml\n   \\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 1 — Fix Issue A: Remove duplicate controller flag\n\nEdit the Deployment to remove the first \\`--watch-ingress-without-class=true\\` entry, keeping only \\`--watch-ingress-without-class=false\\`:\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx patch deployment ingress-nginx-controller \\\\\n  --type=json \\\\\n  -p='[{\"op\":\"remove\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/args/8\"}]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n*(Index 8 is the position of the first \\`--watch-ingress-without-class=true\\`. Verify the index with \\`kubectl get deploy ingress-nginx-controller -o jsonpath=...\\` before applying.)*\n\n### Step 2 — Fix Issue C: Set terminationGracePeriodSeconds\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx patch deployment ingress-nginx-controller \\\\\n  --type=strategic \\\\\n  -p='{\"spec\":{\"template\":{\"spec\":{\"terminationGracePeriodSeconds\":30}}}}'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 3 — Fix Issue B: Correct the nginx IngressClass\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl patch ingressclass nginx \\\\\n  --type=merge \\\\\n  -p='{\"spec\":{\"controller\":\"k8s.io/ingress-nginx\"}}'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 4 — Update the controller image\n\nObtain the new image reference (tag + digest) from the upstream release page, then apply:\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nNEW_IMAGE=\\\"registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:<NEW_TAG>@sha256:<NEW_DIGEST>\\\"\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx set image deployment/ingress-nginx-controller controller=\\$NEW_IMAGE\n\\`\\`\\`\nUpdate the \\`app.kubernetes.io/version\\` label on the Deployment and its Pod template to match the new version for traceability.\n\n### Step 5 — Update RBAC and webhook manifests (if required by changelog)\n\nIf the target release adds new RBAC rules or changes the ValidatingWebhookConfiguration, apply the full upstream deploy manifest for that version (or apply the diff selectively). The safest approach:\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/controller-<NEW_TAG>/deploy/static/provider/kind/deploy.yaml\n\\`\\`\\`\n*Review the manifest before applying to ensure it does not overwrite the custom \\`--publish-status-address=localhost\\` flag or the fixed \\`--watch-ingress-without-class=false\\` flag.*\n\n### Step 6 — Wait for rollout and verify\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deployment/ingress-nginx-controller --timeout=120s\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx get pods\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx logs deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --tail=50\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nExpected log indicators of a clean start:\n- \\\"Starting NGINX Ingress controller\\\"\n- \\\"Backend successfully reloaded\\\"\n- No \\\"ignoring ingressclass\\\" warnings for the \\`nginx\\` class after Step 3.\n\n### Step 7 — Smoke-test ingress routing (if demo app is wired up per Issue D fix)\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n demo exec curl-test -- curl -s -o /dev/null -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\" http://\\$(kubectl -n ingress-nginx get svc ingress-nginx-controller -o jsonpath='{.spec.clusterIP}')/\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Rollback Procedure\n\nIf the rollout produces errors or traffic impact:\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\n# Immediate rollback to previous ReplicaSet\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout undo deployment/ingress-nginx-controller\n\n# Verify rollback is complete\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deployment/ingress-nginx-controller --timeout=60s\n\n# If the IngressClass patch (Step 3) needs reversion:\nkubectl patch ingressclass nginx --type=merge -p='{\\\"spec\\\":{\\\"controller\\\":\\\"k8s.io/ingress-nginx-1\\\"}}'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nThe \\`revisionHistoryLimit: 10\\` on the Deployment ensures the previous ReplicaSet is retained and \\`rollout undo\\` will succeed.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Post-Upgrade Checklist\n\n- [ ] Controller Pod is Running and Ready.\n- [ ] No \\\"ignoring ingressclass\\\" log entries for the \\`nginx\\` IngressClass.\n- [ ] \\`--watch-ingress-without-class\\` appears exactly once in the args (value: \\`false\\`).\n- [ ] \\`terminationGracePeriodSeconds\\` is 30 (or agreed value).\n- [ ] ValidatingWebhookConfiguration caBundle is refreshed (the admission job re-patches it on install).\n- [ ] Demo app Service and Ingress are created (if demo traffic is required).\n- [ ] Old ReplicaSets beyond the desired history limit are pruned if needed.\n- [ ] Backup YAML file archived to the team's change-management store.\n\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap in demo namespace with the full upgrade plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2151,"cache_read_input_tokens":42063,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2151},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0224061-bf49-491a-8f41-89d80269873e","uuid":"d9351608-ad05-4149-974c-b040ce8da604","request_id":"req_011CcRMDSLxWymLpeBzh9GoB"}
